SIMPLE: within
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Within
<hw>With*in"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prep.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>withinne</ets>, <ets>withinnen</ets>, AS. <ets>wi⟦edh⟧innan</ets>;
<ets>wi⟦edh⟧</ets> with, against, toward + <ets>innan</ets> in,
inwardly, within, from <ets>in</ets> in. See <er>With</er>,
<pos>prep.</pos>, <er>In</er>, <pos>prep.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>In the inner or interior part of; inside of; not
without; <as>as, <ex>within</ex> doors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, unhappy youth!⟦br⟧
Come not <qex>within</qex> these doors; <qex>within</qex> this roof⟦br⟧
The enemy of all your graces lives.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Till this be cured by religion, it is as impossible for a man to
be happy -- that is, pleased and contented <qex>within</qex> himself --
as it is for a sick man to be at ease.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the limits or compass of; not further in length
than; <as>as, <ex>within</ex> five miles</as>; not longer in time than;
<as>as, <ex>within</ex> an hour</as>; not exceeding in quantity; <as>as,
expenses kept <ex>within</ex> one's income</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧That he
repair should again <xex>within</xex> a little while.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Within</qex> these five hours lived Lord Hastings,⟦br⟧
Untainted, unexamined, free, at liberty.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, inside the limits, reach, or influence of;
not going outside of; not beyond, overstepping, exceeding, or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Both he and she are still <qex>within</qex> my power.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within himself⟦br⟧
The danger lies, yet lies <qex>within</qex> his power.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Were every action concluded <qex>within</qex> itself, and drew no
consequence after it, we should, undoubtedly, never err in our choice of
good.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Within</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Within
<hw>With*in"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In the inner part;
inwardly; internally.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The wound festers
<xex>within</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Carew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ills from <qex>within</qex> thy reason must prevent.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the house; in doors; <as>as, the master is
<ex>within</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Withinforth</ent>⟦br⟧
